channel.title: ASF Jira
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HIVE-21007] Semi join + Union can lead to wrong plans
item.description:
Tez compiler has the ability to push JOIN within UNION (by replicating join on each branch). If this JOIN had a SJ branch outgoing (or incoming) it could mess up the plan and end up generating incorrect or wrong plan.
As a safe measure any SJ branch after UNION should be removed (until we improve the logic to better handle SJ branches)
item.summary: Semi join + Union can lead to wrong plans

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.
